Overview: Ping will invoke the Pinger operator using the host specified by the
command line parameter and print the results. 

The Pinger operator is a primitive operator written in C++. It will run the
'ping' utility and submit the resulting output as tuple.

1. To build the sample application:
   make

2. To run the sample application:
   ./bin/standalone host=$HOSTNAME

Notes:
  - The command line parameter specifies the host name.
